titleStmt.title: Gothenburg University Library, Gr. 2
titleStmt.sponsor: Greek manuscripts in Sweden – a digitization and cataloguing project

publicationStmt.publisher: Manuscripta.se: A Digital Catalogue of Manuscripts in Sweden

supportDesc.foliation: Foliation in pencil in the upper right margin: 1-122

history.provenance: The codex once belonged to Biblioteca Estense, Mut. II A 14, where it formed the second part of Mut. II A 13; the first part is still in Modena as Mut. Alfa. U. 2. 14. According to Johann Martin Augustin Scholz, who visited Modena around , the manuscript was still there at the time.

p.note: The parchment is well levigate and resistent, but not too thin.

handDesc.handNote: Very neat and small (1 mm) archaizing script, a good imitation of a Perlschrift including the relaxed idiosyncracies of earlier scribes. Prominent csi in three curves. The frequent use of diaeresis is a pointer to the later date.

decoDesc.p: Two shades of red ink: a bright orange for the initials, enlarged in the margins but plain; a magenta colour for the liturgical rubrics in the margins and along the text, incl. chapter divisions.

history.origin: Early 15th c. origin. In Scholz (1823) , the manuscript is collated as having a Constantinopolitan text.

revisionDesc.change: Changing status from draft to published
